<h1 style="text-align: center;"></h1>
<h4><img height="309" src="Images/Colleges_and_Departments/Performing and Visual Arts/FA 100/101130MarriageofFigaro_017.jpg" width="650" /></h4>
<h4></h4>
<h4>FA 100-01</h4>
<p>Only for students who are on campus and on-track for the semester.&nbsp; If you have a class conflict, you can still take section one (see how <a href="x17130.xml">online modules </a>work),<em>&nbsp;</em> and you will need authorization to register for the class, email <a href="mailto:collegepva@byui.edu">Collegepva@byui.edu</a> with your I-number.</p>
<h4>FA 100-02</h4>
<p>Only for students who are off-track or non-traditional students that can attend on-campus events at Brigham Young University Idaho.<em>&nbsp;</em></p>
<h4>FA 100-03 (Long Distance)</h4>
<p>Only for students who are off-track and need to complete their FA 100 requirement from a&nbsp; distance (out of state), this section is partly online.&nbsp; See "<a href="x17132.xml">Distance FA 100-03</a>" for more information about this section.</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"></h1>
<h5>For all three sections, the FA 100 course is not offered as a fully "online" course. Each section requires students to attend:</h5>
<ul>
<li>Six fine art events (either here on campus or in the state they are residing),</li>
<li>Attend or watch a Gospel and Arts lecture,</li>
<li>Complete the four online modules in I-learn. (The online modules are the only part of the course that&nbsp;can be seen as online.)</li>
</ul>
